@rajatsharma Right. I believe that we're not vulnerable here, because we don't use the "spdy" option of the "listen" directive in our configuration file, which you can find here:

https://github.com/gratipay/grtp.co/blob/6bdb5849e8311faacf858eb688e1090bc205b37d/grtp.co-nginx

Do you have evidence that we *are* vulnerable?

@rajatsharma You're quite mistaken. That is the output of `nginx -V`. This is [our configuration file](https://github.com/gratipay/grtp.co/blob/6bdb5849e8311faacf858eb688e1090bc205b37d/grtp.co-nginx):

```
server {
        listen 80;

        listen 443 ssl;

        server_name www.grtp.co;
        server_name gttp.co;
        server_name www.gttp.co;

        ssl_certificate certs/grtp.co.crt;
        ssl_certificate_key certs/grtp.co.key;

        return 302 $scheme://grtp.co$request_uri;
}

server {
        listen 80 default;
        listen 443 ssl;

        server_name grtp.co;

        ssl_certificate certs/grtp.co.crt;
        ssl_certificate_key certs/grtp.co.key;

        root /home/grtp.co/production/www;
        index index.html;

        autoindex on;
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;

        location ~ (widgets/.*\.html|\.json)$ {
                add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin *;
        }

        include mime.types;
        types {
                text/markdown   md;
        }
}
```
